In this statement, the President acknowledges International Holocaust Remembrance Day and honors the memories of the millions of Jews and other victims who lost their lives during the Holocaust. He emphasizes the importance of action in addition to mourning and reflection, and calls on individuals and the international community to resist hate and persecution. The President also highlights the courage of those who resisted the Nazis and commits the United States to standing against any tyrant or dictator who commits crimes against humanity. By remaining vigilant, the President believes we honor those who were lost and ensure their memory lives on for future generations.